== Item Categories ==

Items are organized into functional categories that determine how they can be used:

* '''Weapons''' ($01-$1d) - Offensive equipment for robots. Includes Swords, Axes, Blades, Hammers, Celtis, Punches, Blows, Shots, and Lasers. Higher tier numbers indicate stronger versions.
* '''Bombs''' ($1e-$21) - Consumable explosive items that deal area damage in battle. Can be thrown at enemy groups.
* '''Armor''' ($22-$32) - Defensive equipment including Shields (reduce physical damage), Packs (provide stat bonuses), and Boots (affect movement speed).
* '''Key Items''' ($33-$4f) - Story and progression items that unlock areas, enable abilities, or advance the plot. Cannot be sold or discarded.
* '''Materials''' ($50-$5b) - Scraps and components used in the Invention Machine to create new items. Obtained from enemies or purchased.
* '''Programs''' ($5c-$61) - Consumable items that provide temporary effects or can be used in battle. Include healing, status removal, and attack items.

